# Mistral AI API

_Version: 1.0.0_

Our Chat Completion and Embeddings APIs specification. Create your account on [La Plateforme](https://console.mistral.ai) to get access and read the [docs](https://docs.mistral.ai) to learn how to use it.

Servers

- https://api.mistral.ai

## Global Security

### ApiKey <Pill variant="info">bearer</Pill> <Pill variant="info">http</Pill> \{#ApiKey\}

<Operation>

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>GET</b></Pill> /v1/agents/\{agent\_id\} \{#operation-agents_api_v1_agents_get\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Retrieve an agent entity._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Given an agent retrieve an agent entity with its attributes.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

TypeScript

<SectionContent slot="content" id="operation-agents_api_v1_agents_get_code-samples_typescript">

<TryItNow
  dependencyBundleUrl="/try-it-now/deps.js"
  defaultValue={`import { Mistral } from \"@mistralai/mistralai\";\n\nconst mistral = new Mistral({\n  apiKey: \"MISTRAL_API_KEY\",\n});\n\nasync function run() {\n  const result = await mistral.beta.agents.get({\n    agentId: \"<id>\",\n  });\n\n  console.log(result);\n}\n\nrun();\n`}
/>

</SectionContent>

<SectionTab slot="tab" id="operation-agents_api_v1_agents_get_code-samples_python">

Python

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent slot="content" id="operation-agents_api_v1_agents_get_code-samples_python">

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.agents.get(agent_id="<id>")

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

</CodeSample>

<TryItNow
  dependencyBundleUrl="/try-it-now/deps.js"
  defaultValue={`import { Mistral } from \"@mistralai/mistralai\";\n\nconst mistral = new Mistral({\n  apiKey: \"MISTRAL_API_KEY\",\n});\n\nasync function run() {\n  const result = await mistral.beta.agents.update({\n    agentId: \"<id>\",\n    agentUpdateRequest: {},\n  });\n\n  console.log(result);\n}\n\nrun();\n`}
/>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.agents.update(agent_id="<id>")

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>PATCH</b></Pill> /v1/agents/\{agent\_id\}/version \{#operation-agents_api_v1_agents_update_version\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Update an agent version._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Switch the version of an agent.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<SectionContent

>

<TryItNow
  dependencyBundleUrl="/try-it-now/deps.js"
  defaultValue={`import { Mistral } from \"@mistralai/mistralai\";\n\nconst mistral = new Mistral({\n  apiKey: \"MISTRAL_API_KEY\",\n});\n\nasync function run() {\n  const result = await mistral.beta.agents.updateVersion({\n    agentId: \"<id>\",\n    version: 157995,\n  });\n\n  console.log(result);\n}\n\nrun();\n`}
/>

Python

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_agents_update_version_code-samples_python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.agents.update_version(agent_id="<id>", version=157995)

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.agents.complete(messages=[
        {
            "content": "Who is the best French painter? Answer in one short sentence.",
            "role": "user",
        },
    ], agent_id="<id>", stream=False)

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.agents.list(page=0, page_size=20)

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

<Operation>

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/agents \{#operation-agents_api_v1_agents_create\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Create a agent that can be used within a conversation._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Create a new agent giving it instructions, tools, description. The agent is then available to be used as a regular assistant in a conversation or as part of an agent pool from which it can be used.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<TabbedSection>

<SectionTab slot="tab" id="operation-agents_api_v1_agents_create_code-samples_typescript">

TypeScript

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_agents_create_code-samples_typescript"
>

<TryItNow
  dependencyBundleUrl="/try-it-now/deps.js"
  defaultValue={`import { Mistral } from \"@mistralai/mistralai\";\n\nconst mistral = new Mistral({\n  apiKey: \"MISTRAL_API_KEY\",\n});\n\nasync function run() {\n  const result = await mistral.beta.agents.create({\n    model: \"LeBaron\",\n    name: \"<value>\",\n  });\n\n  console.log(result);\n}\n\nrun();\n`}
/>

</SectionContent>

<SectionTab slot="tab" id="operation-agents_api_v1_agents_create_code-samples_python">

Python

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent slot="content" id="operation-agents_api_v1_agents_create_code-samples_python">

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.agents.create(model="LeBaron", name="<value>")

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

Create Transcription

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<TabbedSection>

<SectionTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-audio_api_v1_transcriptions_post_code-samples_typescript"
>

TypeScript

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-audio_api_v1_transcriptions_post_code-samples_typescript"
>

<TryItNow
  dependencyBundleUrl="/try-it-now/deps.js"
  defaultValue={`import { Mistral } from \"@mistralai/mistralai\";\n\nconst mistral = new Mistral({\n  apiKey: \"MISTRAL_API_KEY\",\n});\n\nasync function run() {\n  const result = await mistral.audio.transcriptions.complete({\n    model: \"Model X\",\n  });\n\n  console.log(result);\n}\n\nrun();\n`}
/>

</SectionContent>

<SectionTab slot="tab" id="operation-audio_api_v1_transcriptions_post_code-samples_python">

Python

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-audio_api_v1_transcriptions_post_code-samples_python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.audio.transcriptions.complete(model="Model X")

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/audio/transcriptions\#stream \{#operation-audio_api_v1_transcriptions_post_stream\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

Create streaming transcription (SSE)

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<TabbedSection>

<SectionTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-audio_api_v1_transcriptions_post_stream_code-samples_typescript"
>

TypeScript

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-audio_api_v1_transcriptions_post_stream_code-samples_typescript"
>

<TryItNow
  dependencyBundleUrl="/try-it-now/deps.js"
  defaultValue={`import { Mistral } from \"@mistralai/mistralai\";\n\nconst mistral = new Mistral({\n  apiKey: \"MISTRAL_API_KEY\",\n});\n\nasync function run() {\n  const result = await mistral.audio.transcriptions.stream({\n    model: \"Camry\",\n  });\n\n  for await (const event of result) {\n    // Handle the event\n    console.log(event);\n  }\n}\n\nrun();\n`}
/>

</SectionContent>

<SectionTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-audio_api_v1_transcriptions_post_stream_code-samples_python"
>

Python

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-audio_api_v1_transcriptions_post_stream_code-samples_python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.audio.transcriptions.stream(model="Camry")

    with res as event_stream:
        for event in event_stream:
            # handle event
            print(event, flush=True)


```

</CodeSample>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.batch.jobs.create(input_files=[
        "fe3343a2-3b8d-404b-ba32-a78dede2614a",
    ], endpoint="/v1/moderations", timeout_hours=24)

    # Handle response
    print(res)
```

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.classifiers.classify_chat(model="Camry", inputs=[
        {
            "messages": [
                {
                    "content": "<value>",
                    "role": "system",
                },
            ],
        },
    ])

    # Handle response
    print(res)
```

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.chat.complete(model="mistral-small-latest", messages=[
        {
            "content": "Who is the best French painter? Answer in one short sentence.",
            "role": "user",
        },
    ], stream=False)

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

</ExpandablePropertyTitle>

<ExpandablePropertyDescription slot="description">

What sampling temperature to use, we recommend between 0.0 and 0.7. Higher values like 0.7 will make the output more random, while lower values like 0.2 will make it more focused and deterministic. ##### top_p \{#operation-chat_completion_v1_chat_completions_post_request_top_p\}

</ExpandablePropertyTitle>

<ExpandablePropertyDescription slot="description">

Nucleus sampling, where the model considers the results of the tokens with `top_p` probability mass. So 0.1 means only the tokens comprising the top 10% probability mass are considered. We generally recommend altering this or `temperature` but not both.

</ExpandablePropertyDescription>

<ExpandablePropertyDefaultValue slot="defaultValue">

_Default Value:_ `1`

</ExpandablePropertyDefaultValue>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.classifiers.moderate_chat(inputs=[
        {
            "content": "<value>",
            "role": "tool",
        },
    ], model="LeBaron")

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

<Operation>

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>GET</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\}/history \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_history\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Retrieve all entries in a conversation._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Given a conversation_id retrieve all the entries belonging to that conversation. The entries are sorted in the order they were appended, those can be messages, connectors or function_call.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<TryItNow
  dependencyBundleUrl="/try-it-now/deps.js"
  defaultValue={`import { Mistral } from \"@mistralai/mistralai\";\n\nconst mistral = new Mistral({\n  apiKey: \"MISTRAL_API_KEY\",\n});\n\nasync function run() {\n  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.getHistory({\n    conversationId: \"<id>\",\n  });\n\n  console.log(result);\n}\n\nrun();\n`}
/>

Python

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_history_code-samples_python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.get_history(conversation_id="<id>")

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>GET</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\}/messages \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_messages\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Retrieve all messages in a conversation._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Given a conversation_id retrieve all the messages belonging to that conversation. This is similar to retrieving all entries except we filter the messages only.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<TabbedSection>

<TryItNow
  dependencyBundleUrl="/try-it-now/deps.js"
  defaultValue={`import { Mistral } from \"@mistralai/mistralai\";\n\nconst mistral = new Mistral({\n  apiKey: \"MISTRAL_API_KEY\",\n});\n\nasync function run() {\n  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.getMessages({\n    conversationId: \"<id>\",\n  });\n\n  console.log(result);\n}\n\nrun();\n`}
/>

Python

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_messages_code-samples_python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.get_messages(conversation_id="<id>")

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\} \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Append new entries to an existing conversation._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Run completion on the history of the conversation and the user entries. Return the new created entries.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<TabbedSection>

<SectionTab
  slot="tab"

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_code-samples_typescript"
>

<TryItNow
  dependencyBundleUrl="/try-it-now/deps.js"
  defaultValue={`import { Mistral } from \"@mistralai/mistralai\";\n\nconst mistral = new Mistral({\n  apiKey: \"MISTRAL_API_KEY\",\n});\n\nasync function run() {\n  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.append({\n    conversationId: \"<id>\",\n    conversationAppendRequest: {\n      inputs: [],\n    },\n  });\n\n  console.log(result);\n}\n\nrun();\n`}
/>

</SectionContent>

<SectionTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_code-samples_python"
>

Python

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_code-samples_python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.append(conversation_id="<id>", inputs=[], stream=False, store=True, handoff_execution="server")

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

</CodeSample>

<Operation>

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\}/restart \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Restart a conversation starting from a given entry._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Given a conversation_id and an id, recreate a conversation from this point and run completion. A new conversation is returned with the new entries returned.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<TabbedSection>

<SectionTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_code-samples_typescript"
>

TypeScript

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_code-samples_typescript"
>

<TryItNow
  dependencyBundleUrl="/try-it-now/deps.js"
  defaultValue={`import { Mistral } from \"@mistralai/mistralai\";\n\nconst mistral = new Mistral({\n  apiKey: \"MISTRAL_API_KEY\",\n});\n\nasync function run() {\n  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.restart({\n    conversationId: \"<id>\",\n    conversationRestartRequest: {\n      inputs: \"<value>\",\n      fromEntryId: \"<id>\",\n    },\n  });\n\n  console.log(result);\n}\n\nrun();\n`}
/>

</SectionContent>

<SectionTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_code-samples_python"
>

Python

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_code-samples_python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.restart(conversation_id="<id>", inputs="<value>", from_entry_id="<id>", stream=False, store=True, handoff_execution="server")

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

</CodeSample>

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\}/restart\#stream \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_stream\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Restart a conversation starting from a given entry._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Given a conversation_id and an id, recreate a conversation from this point and run completion. A new conversation is returned with the new entries returned.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<TabbedSection>

<SectionTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_stream_code-samples_typescript"
>

TypeScript

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_stream_code-samples_typescript"
>

<TryItNow
  dependencyBundleUrl="/try-it-now/deps.js"
  defaultValue={`import { Mistral } from \"@mistralai/mistralai\";\n\nconst mistral = new Mistral({\n  apiKey: \"MISTRAL_API_KEY\",\n});\n\nasync function run() {\n  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.restartStream({\n    conversationId: \"<id>\",\n    conversationRestartStreamRequest: {\n      inputs: [\n        {\n          object: \"entry\",\n          type: \"message.input\",\n          role: \"assistant\",\n          content: \"<value>\",\n          prefix: false,\n        },\n      ],\n      fromEntryId: \"<id>\",\n    },\n  });\n\n  for await (const event of result) {\n    // Handle the event\n    console.log(event);\n  }\n}\n\nrun();\n`}
/>

</SectionContent>

<SectionTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_stream_code-samples_python"
>

Python

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_stream_code-samples_python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.restart_stream(conversation_id="<id>", inputs=[
        {
            "object": "entry",
            "type": "message.input",
            "role": "assistant",
            "content": "<value>",
            "prefix": False,
        },
    ], from_entry_id="<id>", stream=True, store=True, handoff_execution="server")

    with res as event_stream:
        for event in event_stream:
            # handle event
            print(event, flush=True)


```

</CodeSample>

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\}\#stream \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_stream\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Append new entries to an existing conversation._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Run completion on the history of the conversation and the user entries. Return the new created entries.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<TabbedSection>

<SectionTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_stream_code-samples_typescript"
>

TypeScript

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_stream_code-samples_typescript"
>

<TryItNow
  dependencyBundleUrl="/try-it-now/deps.js"
  defaultValue={`import { Mistral } from \"@mistralai/mistralai\";\n\nconst mistral = new Mistral({\n  apiKey: \"MISTRAL_API_KEY\",\n});\n\nasync function run() {\n  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.appendStream({\n    conversationId: \"<id>\",\n    conversationAppendStreamRequest: {\n      inputs: \"<value>\",\n    },\n  });\n\n  for await (const event of result) {\n    // Handle the event\n    console.log(event);\n  }\n}\n\nrun();\n`}
/>

</SectionContent>

<SectionTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_stream_code-samples_python"
>

Python

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_stream_code-samples_python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.append_stream(conversation_id="<id>", inputs="<value>", stream=True, store=True, handoff_execution="server")

    with res as event_stream:
        for event in event_stream:
            # handle event
            print(event, flush=True)


```

</CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.list(page=0, page_size=100)

    # Handle response
    print(res)
```

<Operation>

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Create a conversation and append entries to it._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Create a new conversation, using a base model or an agent and append entries. Completion and tool executions are run and the response is appended to the conversation.Use the returned conversation_id to continue the conversation.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<TabbedSection>

<SectionTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_code-samples_typescript"
>

TypeScript

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_code-samples_typescript"
>

<TryItNow
  dependencyBundleUrl="/try-it-now/deps.js"
  defaultValue={`import { Mistral } from \"@mistralai/mistralai\";\n\nconst mistral = new Mistral({\n  apiKey: \"MISTRAL_API_KEY\",\n});\n\nasync function run() {\n  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.start({\n    inputs: \"<value>\",\n  });\n\n  console.log(result);\n}\n\nrun();\n`}
/>

</SectionContent>

<SectionTab slot="tab" id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_code-samples_python">

Python

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_code-samples_python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.start(inputs="<value>", stream=False)

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

</CodeSample>

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations\#stream \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_stream\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Create a conversation and append entries to it._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Create a new conversation, using a base model or an agent and append entries. Completion and tool executions are run and the response is appended to the conversation.Use the returned conversation_id to continue the conversation.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<TabbedSection>

<SectionTab
  slot="tab"

TypeScript

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_stream_code-samples_typescript"
>

<TryItNow
  dependencyBundleUrl="/try-it-now/deps.js"
  defaultValue={`import { Mistral } from \"@mistralai/mistralai\";\n\nconst mistral = new Mistral({\n  apiKey: \"MISTRAL_API_KEY\",\n});\n\nasync function run() {\n  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.startStream({\n    inputs: [\n      {\n        object: \"entry\",\n        type: \"agent.handoff\",\n        previousAgentId: \"<id>\",\n        previousAgentName: \"<value>\",\n        nextAgentId: \"<id>\",\n        nextAgentName: \"<value>\",\n      },\n    ],\n  });\n\n  for await (const event of result) {\n    // Handle the event\n    console.log(event);\n  }\n}\n\nrun();\n`}
/>

</SectionContent>

<SectionTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_stream_code-samples_python"
>

Python

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_stream_code-samples_python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.start_stream(inputs=[
        {
            "object": "entry",
            "type": "function.result",
            "tool_call_id": "<id>",
            "result": "<value>",
        },
    ], stream=True)

    with res as event_stream:
        for event in event_stream:
            # handle event
            print(event, flush=True)


```

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.embeddings.create(model="mistral-embed", inputs=[
        "Embed this sentence.",
        "As well as this one.",
    ])

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Upload a file that can be used across various endpoints.

The size of individual files can be a maximum of 512 MB. The Fine-tuning API only supports .jsonl files.

Please contact us if you need to increase these storage limits.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

  slot="content"
  id="operation-files_api_routes_upload_file_code-samples_typescript"

<TryItNow
  dependencyBundleUrl="/try-it-now/deps.js"
  defaultValue={`import { Mistral } from \"@mistralai/mistralai\";\nimport { openAsBlob } from \"node:fs\";\n\nconst mistral = new Mistral({\n  apiKey: \"MISTRAL_API_KEY\",\n});\n\nasync function run() {\n  const result = await mistral.files.upload({\n    file: await openAsBlob(\"example.file\"),\n  });\n\n  console.log(result);\n}\n\nrun();\n`}
/>

</SectionContent>

<SectionTab slot="tab" id="operation-files_api_routes_upload_file_code-samples_python">

Python

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent slot="content" id="operation-files_api_routes_upload_file_code-samples_python">

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.files.upload(file={
        "file_name": "example.file",
        "content": open("example.file", "rb"),
    })

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

</CodeSample>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.fim.complete(model="codestral-2405", prompt="def", top_p=1, stream=False, suffix="return a+b")

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

<ExpandablePropertyTitle slot="title">

##### stream \{#operation-fim_completion_v1_fim_completions_post_request_stream\}

</ExpandablePropertyTitle>

<ExpandablePropertyDescription slot="description">

Whether to stream back partial progress. If set, tokens will be sent as data-only server-side events as they become available, with the stream terminated by a data: [DONE] message. Otherwise, the server will hold the request open until the timeout or until completion, with the response containing the full result as JSON.

</ExpandablePropertyDescription>

_Default Value:_ `false`

</ExpandablePropertyDefaultValue>

<ExpandablePropertyTitle slot="title">

##### suffix \{#operation-fim_completion_v1_fim_completions_post_request_suffix\}

</ExpandablePropertyTitle>

<ExpandablePropertyDescription slot="description">

Optional text/code that adds more context for the model. When given a `prompt` and a `suffix` the model will fill what is between them. When `suffix` is not provided, the model will simply execute completion starting with `prompt`.

</ExpandablePropertyDescription>

<ExpandablePropertyExamples slot="examples">

_Example:_

```
return a+b
```

</ExpandablePropertyExamples>

</ExpandableProperty>

  slot="entry"

  typeInfo={{"label":"union","linkedLabel":"union","children":[{"label":"number","linkedLabel":"number","children":[],"breakoutSubTypes":{}},{"label":"null","linkedLabel":"null","children":[],"breakoutSubTypes":{}}],"breakoutSubTypes":{}}}
  typeAnnotations={[]}
  hasExpandableContent={true}
  expandByDefault={true}
>

<ExpandablePropertyTitle slot="title">

##### temperature \{#operation-fim_completion_v1_fim_completions_post_request_temperature\}

</ExpandablePropertyTitle>

<ExpandablePropertyDescription slot="description">

What sampling temperature to use, we recommend between 0.0 and 0.7. Higher values like 0.7 will make the output more random, while lower values like 0.2 will make it more focused and deterministic. We generally recommend altering this or `top_p` but not both. The default value varies depending on the model you are targeting. Call the `/models` endpoint to retrieve the appropriate value.

</ExpandablePropertyDescription>

</ExpandableProperty>

<ExpandableProperty
  slot="entry"
  id="top_p"
  headingId="operation-fim_completion_v1_fim_completions_post_request_top_p"
  typeInfo={{"label":"number","linkedLabel":"number","children":[],"breakoutSubTypes":{}}}
  typeAnnotations={[{"title":"Min: 0","variant":"warning"},{"title":"Max: 1","variant":"warning"}]}
  hasExpandableContent={true}
  expandByDefault={true}
>

<ExpandablePropertyTitle slot="title">

##### top_p \{#operation-fim_completion_v1_fim_completions_post_request_top_p\}

</ExpandablePropertyTitle>

<ExpandablePropertyDescription slot="description">

Nucleus sampling, where the model considers the results of the tokens with `top_p` probability mass. So 0.1 means only the tokens comprising the top 10% probability mass are considered. We generally recommend altering this or `temperature` but not both.

</ExpandablePropertyDescription>

<ExpandablePropertyDefaultValue slot="defaultValue">

_Default Value:_ `1`

</ExpandablePropertyDefaultValue>

</ExpandableProperty>

```python
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.fine_tuning.jobs.cancel(job_id="6188a2f6-7513-4e0f-89cc-3f8088523a49")

    # Handle response
    print(res)
```

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.fine_tuning.jobs.list(page=0, page_size=100, created_by_me=False)

    # Handle response
    print(res)
```

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/fine\_tuning/jobs \{#operation-jobs_api_routes_fine_tuning_create_fine_tuning_job\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Create Fine Tuning Job_

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Create a new fine-tuning job, it will be queued for processing.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<TabbedSection>

<SectionTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-jobs_api_routes_fine_tuning_create_fine_tuning_job_code-samples_typescript"
>

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-jobs_api_routes_fine_tuning_create_fine_tuning_job_code-samples_typescript"
>

<TryItNow
  dependencyBundleUrl="/try-it-now/deps.js"
  defaultValue={`import { Mistral } from \"@mistralai/mistralai\";\n\nconst mistral = new Mistral({\n  apiKey: \"MISTRAL_API_KEY\",\n});\n\nasync function run() {\n  const result = await mistral.fineTuning.jobs.create({\n    model: \"Camaro\",\n    hyperparameters: {\n      learningRate: 0.0001,\n    },\n  });\n\n  console.log(result);\n}\n\nrun();\n`}
/>

</SectionContent>

<SectionTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-jobs_api_routes_fine_tuning_create_fine_tuning_job_code-samples_python"
>

Python

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-jobs_api_routes_fine_tuning_create_fine_tuning_job_code-samples_python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.fine_tuning.jobs.create(model="Camaro", hyperparameters={
        "learning_rate": 0.0001,
    }, invalid_sample_skip_percentage=0)

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```

</CodeSample>

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Delete a library and all of it's document._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Given a library id, deletes it together with all documents that have been uploaded to that library.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

```python
    # Handle response
```

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/libraries/\{library\_id\}/documents \{#operation-libraries_documents_upload_v1\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Upload a new document._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Given a library, upload a new document to that library. It is queued for processing, it status will change it has been processed. The processing has to be completed in order be discoverable for the library search

</OperationDescriptionSection>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.libraries.documents.upload(library_id="a02150d9-5ee0-4877-b62c-28b1fcdf3b76", file={
        "file_name": "example.file",
        "content": open("example.file", "rb"),
    })

    # Handle response
    print(res)
```

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>PUT</b></Pill> /v1/libraries/\{library\_id\}/share \{#operation-libraries_share_create_v1\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Create or update an access level._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Given a library id, you can create or update the access level of an entity. You have to be owner of the library to share a library. An owner cannot change their own role. A library cannot be shared outside of the organization.

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/libraries \{#operation-libraries_create_v1\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Create a new Library._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Create a new Library, you will be marked as the owner and only you will have the possibility to share it with others. When first created this will only be accessible by you.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

TypeScript

<SectionContent slot="content" id="operation-libraries_create_v1_code-samples_typescript">

<TryItNow
  dependencyBundleUrl="/try-it-now/deps.js"
  defaultValue={`import { Mistral } from \"@mistralai/mistralai\";\n\nconst mistral = new Mistral({\n  apiKey: \"MISTRAL_API_KEY\",\n});\n\nasync function run() {\n  const result = await mistral.beta.libraries.create({\n    name: \"<value>\",\n  });\n\n  console.log(result);\n}\n\nrun();\n`}
/>

</SectionContent>

Python

<SectionContent slot="content" id="operation-libraries_create_v1_code-samples_python">

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral
import os


with Mistral(
    api_key=os.getenv("MISTRAL_API_KEY", ""),
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.libraries.create(name="<value>")

    # Handle response
    print(res)


```
